					<description><![CDATA[This is just a warning for readers of the Stacks project: please be careful as I think I don&#8217;t know left from right. As a consequence, the text of the Stacks project sometimes uses the phrase &#8220;section&#8221; when it should &#8230; <a href="https://www.math.columbia.edu/~dejong/wordpress/?p=4798">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This is just a warning for readers of the Stacks project: please be careful as I think I don&#8217;t know left from right. As a consequence, the text of the Stacks project sometimes uses the phrase &#8220;section&#8221; when it should be using &#8220;retraction&#8221;. Similarly, watch out for confusion between &#8220;left inverse&#8221; and &#8220;right inverse&#8221;.</p>
<p>If you find occurrences of this, just leave a comment to point it out and we&#8217;ll fix it.</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
